🧨 STEP 5: FULL AUTHENTICATION VULNERABILITY COVERAGE

You MUST check ALL:

---

5.1 Weak Credential Handling

- Plaintext passwords
- Weak hashing (MD5, SHA1)
- Missing salting
- Hardcoded credentials

---

5.2 Broken Authentication Logic

- Authentication bypass
- Missing checks
- Improper condition handling

---

5.3 Brute Force Vulnerability

- No rate limiting
- No account lockout
- No CAPTCHA or throttling

---

5.4 Session Mismanagement

- Predictable session IDs
- Session fixation
- Missing expiration
- Insecure cookie flags

---

5.5 Token Issues (JWT/API Tokens)

- Missing signature validation
- Weak secrets
- No expiration
- Algorithm confusion

---

5.6 Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) Issues

- Missing MFA where required
- MFA bypass
- Weak OTP handling

---

5.7 Default / Hardcoded Credentials

- Embedded usernames/passwords
- Default admin accounts

---

5.8 Improper Password Policies

- Weak password rules
- No complexity enforcement

---

5.9 Credential Exposure

- Logging passwords
- Returning sensitive data in responses

---

5.10 Authentication State Flaws

- Improper logout
- Session reuse
- Parallel session misuse

---

🛡️ STEP 6: MITIGATION VALIDATION

SAFE CONTROLS:

- Strong hashing (bcrypt, Argon2)
- Proper session handling
- Token validation
- MFA enforcement
- Rate limiting

---

UNSAFE CONTROLS:

- Custom crypto
- Weak hashing
- Client-side-only validation

---

DECISION:

- Proper controls → Protected
- Weak/missing → Vulnerable
- Cannot verify → Not Confirmed

